        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 1:23PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 122 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Round Oak to near Bolingbroke, and moving
southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Macon, Gray, Payne, Payne City, Postell, Lake Tobesofkee, Bradley,
Wayside, Mountain Springs, Griswoldville, Round Oak, Wesleyan,
Arkwright, Skipperton, James, Bolingbroke, Dames Ferry, Rutland,
Haddock, and Greenberry Crossroads.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
